    <h1>Harmful Language: Definitions & Categories</h1>

    <p>
        Harmful language refers to any expression that causes psychological, emotional, 
        social, or physical harm. Categorising harmful language helps moderation, 
        analysis, and developing safer online environments.
    </p>

    <!-- Category Sections -->
    <div class="category">
        <h2>1. Abusive / Insulting Language</h2>
        <p>Language intended to belittle or demean an individual.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “You’re so useless; nobody wants you on this team.”</div>
        <p><strong>Key Features:</strong> Personal insults, name-calling.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>2. Hate Speech</h2>
        <p>Hostile language targeting protected characteristics (race, religion, etc.).</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “People from that ethnic group are not welcome here.”</div>
        <p><strong>Key Features:</strong> Identity-based attack, discrimination.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>3. Dehumanisation</h2>
        <p>Comparing individuals to animals or sub-human beings.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “They’re like animals; they don’t deserve rights.”</div>
        <p><strong>Key Features:</strong> Removal of dignity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>4. Threats / Harassment</h2>
        <p>Language expressing intent to harm or intimidate.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “I'm going to come after you if you post that again.”</div>
        <p><strong>Key Features:</strong> Intimidation, harmful intent.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>5. Toxic Aggression</h2>
        <p>Highly hostile language meant to provoke conflict.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “You’re pathetic—just get lost already!”</div>
        <p><strong>Key Features:</strong> Aggressive tone, hostility.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>6. Neutral / Non-harmful</h2>
        <p>Respectful, safe, factual communication.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “I don’t agree with your opinion, but I see your point.”</div>
    </div>

    <div class="category">
        <h2>7. Ambiguous</h2>
        <p>Meaning unclear without context.</p>
        <div class="example-box">Example: “Watch yourself next time.”</div>
    </div>

